race.comment: The well-related ZARIPPA (4) (half to 2xG3 winner I'm A Rippa) has gotten better with each run this time in and looks to be building up to another victory. Drawn to sit up on speed from the inside alley and should give backers a sight. Former NSW galloper GONE TO CAPE YORK (2) is having his first run for the new stable but has revved up for this with two recent trials and will find this task easier than what he faced when last in work. Respect any market confidence. SHOW ME THE STARS (11) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on. KEEPMEINTHELOPE (5) now joins the Currie stable after beginning his career for the Kendrick barn. Looks to have found a suitable race this time and is not to be discounted.
